- @title = "Documentation"
.container
  .row
    .col-md-12
      %h3 Documentation
      %p Netzke components consist of server side (Ruby) and client side (JavaScript) code, each having an API that you will want to use in your app.
      %h4 Server-side docs

      %p
        #{link_to 'Netzke Core', 'http://www.rubydoc.info/github/netzke/netzke-core'} is the barebones of the framework, the base for building components
      %p
        #{link_to 'Netzke Basepack', 'http://www.rubydoc.info/github/netzke/netzke-basepack'} provides a few essential, full-featured components that can be used as building blocks for your apps

      %h4 Client-side docs
      #{link_to 'These docs', 'http://api.netzke.org/client/'} (combining Core and Basepack) should be consulted for client-side API.

      %h3 Tutorials and guides
      %p #{link_to 'Netzke Blog', 'http://blog.netzke.org'} contains the most recent tutorials, guides, and development tips.
      %p #{link_to 'Netzke Wiki', 'https://github.com/netzke/netzke/wiki'} contains community-editable guides.
      %p #{link_to 'Getting started with Netzke', 'https://www.airpair.com/javascript/posts/getting-started-with-netzke'} on airpair (an update for 1.0 is pending for publishing)
      %p #{link_to 'Write Less Code Blog', 'http://writelesscode.com/'} has many (outdated) tutorials.
